                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d223">
                <head>223. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d223fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 330.13/6–457. Top Secret; <gloss target="#t_niact1">Niact</gloss>.
                        Drafted by the President.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1957-06-04T19:59:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 4, 1957—7:59 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8482. Eyes only for <persName corresp="#p_SHE1">Stassen</persName> from
                    Secretary. With the personal approval of the President I send you the following
                    instructions:</p>
                <p>You will notify Mr. <persName corresp="#p_ZVA1">Zorin</persName> at the earliest
                    possible moment that the memorandum you submitted to him was not only informal
                    and unofficial, but had no approval in its submitted form either by the
                    President or the State Department, and that there are some aspects of the
                    memorandum to which this government cannot agree at this moment. Therefore, you
                    will request that Mr. <persName corresp="#p_ZVA1">Zorin</persName> return the
                    memorandum.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
